The paper focuses on object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel few-shot adaptation approach, which involves adapting a pre-trained model to a new domain with limited labeled data, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses multiple datasets to evaluate the proposed method, which is common in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
